<subSubSection pageId="79" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="79.[151,1437,151,1726]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[573,705,294,320]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Arctic Cod</emphasis>
or Polar Cod. To 
<quantity box="[907,976,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="cm" value="46.0">46 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[992,1073,295,322]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5974" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="in" value="18.1">18.1 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Wienerroither" box="[1135,1424,295,321]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Wienerroither" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 2011" refId="ref333424" refString="Wienerroither, R., Johanneson, E., Langoy, H., Erikson, K. B., de Lange Wenneck, T., Hoines, A. &amp; Bjelland, O. (2011) Atlas of the Barents Sea fishes. IMR / PINRO Joint Report Series, 1 - 2011." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Wienerroither 
<emphasis box="[1301,1358,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), usually less than 
<quantity box="[385,452,330,357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="cm" value="25.0">25 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[465,530,331,358]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4892" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="in" value="9.8">9.8 in</quantity>
) (Cohen in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cohen" box="[658,856,331,357]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cohen" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" refId="ref271020" refString="Cohen, D. M., Inada, T., Iwamoto, T. &amp; Scialabba, N. (1990) FAO Species Catalogue. Gadiform Fishes of the World. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 10. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1990">
Cohen 
<emphasis box="[736,791,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
). The largest we know of from our area is a specimen from the Chukchi Sea measuring 
<quantity box="[583,653,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[671,732,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.048" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="in" value="12.0">12 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Alverson and Wilimovsky" box="[798,1166,367,394]" firstAuthor="Alverson" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="843 - 860" refId="ref259895" refString="Alverson, D. L. &amp; Wilimovsky, N. J. (1966) Fishery investigations of the southeastern Chukchi Sea. In: Wilimovsky, N. J. &amp; Wolfe, N. (Eds), Environment of the Cape Thompson Region, Alaska. United States Atomic Energy Commission, p. 843 - 860." type="book chapter" year="1966">Alverson and Wilimovsky 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Circumpolar in Arctic (Cohen in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cohen" box="[316,518,403,429]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cohen" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" refId="ref271020" refString="Cohen, D. M., Inada, T., Iwamoto, T. &amp; Scialabba, N. (1990) FAO Species Catalogue. Gadiform Fishes of the World. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 10. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1990">
Cohen 
<emphasis box="[396,452,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
); Arctic Siberia to 
<collectingRegion box="[728,786,403,429]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Cape</collectingRegion>
Olyutorskiy, western Bering Sea; Beaufort Sea (Frost and Lowry 1981) to 
<collectingRegion box="[382,458,439,465]" country="United Kingdom" name="City of Bristol" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Bristol</collectingRegion>
Bay, south-eastern Bering Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Allen and Smith" box="[818,1072,439,465]" firstAuthor="Allen" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" refId="ref259821" refString="Allen, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. B. (1988) Atlas and zoogeography of common fishes in the Bering Sea and northeastern Pacific. NOAA Technical Report NMFS, 66." type="book" year="1988">
Allen and 
<collectingRegion box="[937,1004,439,465]" country="Bermuda" name="Smith's" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Smith</collectingRegion>
1988
</bibRefCitation>
). Taken as far north as 
<geoCoordinate box="[1332,1431,439,465]" degrees="88" direction="north" minutes="26" orientation="latitude" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" precision="925" value="88.433334">88°26’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[198,305,475,501]" degrees="126" direction="east" minutes="26" orientation="longitude" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" precision="925" value="126.433334">126°26’E</geoCoordinate>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mecklenburg" box="[319,598,475,501]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Mecklenburg" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="168 - 187" refId="ref300875" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W., Stein, D. L., Sheiko, B. A., Chernova, N. V., Mecklenburg, T. A. &amp; Holladay, B. A. (2007) Russian-American long-term census of the Arctic: benthic fishes trawled in the Chukchi Sea and Bering Sea, August 2004. Northwestern Naturalist, 88, 168 - 187. https: // doi. org / 10.1898 / 1051 - 1733 (2007) 88 [168: rlcota] 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2007">
Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[476,531,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). Brackish lagoons, river mouths (
<bibRefCitation author="Morrow" box="[976,1135,475,501]" firstAuthor="Morrow" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" refId="ref303568" refString="Morrow, J. E. (1980) The Freshwater Fishes of Alaska. Alaska Northwest Publishing Company, Anchorage." type="book" year="1980">Morrow 1980</bibRefCitation>
), and ocean; depth: surface to at least 
<quantity box="[312,404,511,537]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.39" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="m" value="1390.0">1,390 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[419,509,510,538]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3895832" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="ft" value="4559.0">4,559 ft</quantity>
) (min.: Renaud in 
<bibRefCitation author="Coad and Reist" box="[720,957,511,537]" firstAuthor="Coad" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" refId="ref270835" refString="Coad, B. W. &amp; Reist, J. D. (Eds.). (2018) Marine Fishes of Arctic Canada. University of Toronto Press, Toronto." type="book" year="2018">Coad and Reist 2018</bibRefCitation>
; max.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Mecklenburg" box="[1039,1317,511,537]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Mecklenburg" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="109 - 140" refId="ref300975" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W., Moller, P. R. &amp; Steinke, D. (2011) Biodiversity of arctic marine fishes: taxonomy and zoogeography. Marine Biodiversity, 41, 109 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 010 - 0070 - z" type="journal article" year="2011">
Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[1194,1251,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
